Module paceManager
Package data

Class Team

java.lang.Object
data.Team
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Team extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a single team in a given competition. A team is composed of one or more riders, is given a team number and division, and stores additional values pertaining to the pace
Author:
Thomas Kwashnak

  • Method Details

    • getDivision

      public Division getDivision()
      Attempts to return the division of the pace
      Returns:
      The team's division, if it is referenced by the pointer. Returns null if the pointer does not have a reference to the division.

    • getDivisionPointer

      public DivisionPointer getDivisionPointer()
      Returns the raw pointer to the team's division
      Returns:
      The division pointer, which should have a reference to the team's division, or at least have the UUID of the proper division.

    • lookupDivision

      public void lookupDivision(@NotNull @NotNull Iterable<Division> divisions)
      Updates the team's division pointer from a provided list of divisions. If one of the divisions provided has the same UUID as the current pointer, then the team sets its current pointer to that division.
      Parameters:
      divisions - List of divisions (as an Iterable) to check division UUIDs with.

    • getElapsedTime

      public Time getElapsedTime()
      Gets the elapsed time between the start and the end time. Only returns the elapsed time if both times are not null
      Returns:
      The elapsed time between the start and end time. Returns null if either or both start and end times are null.
